  25 def startswith(string, incomplete):
  26     """Returns True when string starts with incomplete
  27 
  28     It might be overridden with a fuzzier version - for example a case insensitive version
  29 
  30     Parameters
  31     ----------
  32     string : str
  33         The string to check
  34     incomplete : str
  35         The incomplete string to compare to the begining of string
  36 
  37     Returns
  38     -------
  39     bool
  40         True if string starts with incomplete, False otherwise
  41     """
  42     return string.startswith(incomplete)

  45 class CompletionConfiguration(object):
  46     """A class to hold the completion configuration
  47 
  48     Attributes
  49     ----------
  50 
  51     complete_options : bool
  52         Wether to complete the options or not. By default, the options are only completed after the user has entered
  53         a first dash '-'. Change this value to True to always complete the options, even without first typing any
  54         character.
  55     match_incomplete : func
  56         A function use to check whether a parameter match an incomplete argument typed by the user
  57     """
  58     def __init__(self):
  59         self.complete_options = False
  60         self.match_incomplete = startswith
  61

  63 def match(string, incomplete):
  64     import click_completion
  65     # backward compatibility handling
  66     if click_completion.startswith != startswith:
  67         fn = click_completion.startswith
  68     else:
  69         fn = completion_configuration.match_incomplete
  70     return fn(string, incomplete)

  73 def get_choices(cli, prog_name, args, incomplete):
  74     """
  75 
  76     Parameters
  77     ----------
  78     cli : click.Command
  79         The main click Command of the program
  80     prog_name : str
  81         The program name on the command line
  82     args : [str]
  83         The arguments already written by the user on the command line
  84     incomplete : str
  85         The partial argument to complete
  86 
  87     Returns
  88     -------
  89     [(str, str)]
  90         A list of completion results. The first element of each tuple is actually the argument to complete, the second
  91         element is an help string for this argument.
  92     """
  93     ctx = resolve_ctx(cli, prog_name, args)
  94     if ctx is None:
  95         return
  96     optctx = None
  97     if args:
  98         options = [param
  99                    for param in ctx.command.get_params(ctx)
 100                    if isinstance(param, Option)]
 101         arguments = [param
 102                      for param in ctx.command.get_params(ctx)
 103                      if isinstance(param, Argument)]
 104         for param in options:
 105             if not param.is_flag and args[-1] in param.opts + param.secondary_opts:
 106                 optctx = param
 107         if optctx is None:
 108             for param in arguments:
 109                 if (
 110                         not incomplete.startswith("-")
 111                         and (
 112                             ctx.params.get(param.name) in (None, ())
 113                             or param.nargs == -1
 114                         )
 115                 ):
 116                     optctx = param
 117                     break
 118     choices = []
 119     if optctx:
 120         choices += [c if isinstance(c, tuple) else (c, None) for c in optctx.type.complete(ctx, incomplete)]
 121     else:
 122         for param in ctx.command.get_params(ctx):
 123             if (completion_configuration.complete_options or incomplete and not incomplete[:1].isalnum()) and isinstance(param, Option):
 124                 # filter hidden click.Option
 125                 if getattr(param, 'hidden', False):
 126                     continue
 127                 for opt in param.opts:
 128                     if match(opt, incomplete):
 129                         choices.append((opt, param.help))
 130                 for opt in param.secondary_opts:
 131                     if match(opt, incomplete):
 132                         # don't put the doc so fish won't group the primary and
 133                         # and secondary options
 134                         choices.append((opt, None))
 135         if isinstance(ctx.command, MultiCommand):
 136             for name in ctx.command.list_commands(ctx):
 137                 if match(name, incomplete):
 138                     choices.append((name, ctx.command.get_command_short_help(ctx, name)))
 139 
 140     for item, help in choices:
 141         yield (item, help)
 142

 144 def do_bash_complete(cli, prog_name):
 145     """Do the completion for bash
 146 
 147     Parameters
 148     ----------
 149     cli : click.Command
 150         The main click Command of the program
 151     prog_name : str
 152         The program name on the command line
 153 
 154     Returns
 155     -------
 156     bool
 157         True if the completion was successful, False otherwise
 158     """
 159     comp_words = os.environ['COMP_WORDS']
 160     try:
 161         cwords = shlex.split(comp_words)
 162         quoted = False
 163     except ValueError:  # No closing quotation
 164         cwords = split_args(comp_words)
 165         quoted = True
 166     cword = int(os.environ['COMP_CWORD'])
 167     args = cwords[1:cword]
 168     try:
 169         incomplete = cwords[cword]
 170     except IndexError:
 171         incomplete = ''
 172     choices = get_choices(cli, prog_name, args, incomplete)
 173 
 174     if quoted:
 175         echo('\t'.join(opt for opt, _ in choices), nl=False)
 176     else:
 177         echo('\t'.join(re.sub(r"""([\s\\"'()])""", r'\\\1', opt) for opt, _ in choices), nl=False)
 178 
 179     return True
 180

 182 def do_fish_complete(cli, prog_name):
 183     """Do the fish completion
 184 
 185     Parameters
 186     ----------
 187     cli : click.Command
 188         The main click Command of the program
 189     prog_name : str
 190         The program name on the command line
 191 
 192     Returns
 193     -------
 194     bool
 195         True if the completion was successful, False otherwise
 196     """
 197     commandline = os.environ['COMMANDLINE']
 198     args = split_args(commandline)[1:]
 199     if args and not commandline.endswith(' '):
 200         incomplete = args[-1]
 201         args = args[:-1]
 202     else:
 203         incomplete = ''
 204 
 205     for item, help in get_choices(cli, prog_name, args, incomplete):
 206         if help:
 207             echo("%s\t%s" % (item, re.sub(r'\s', ' ', help)))
 208         else:
 209             echo(item)
 210 
 211     return True

 214 def do_zsh_complete(cli, prog_name):
 215     """Do the zsh completion
 216 
 217     Parameters
 218     ----------
 219     cli : click.Command
 220         The main click Command of the program
 221     prog_name : str
 222         The program name on the command line
 223 
 224     Returns
 225     -------
 226     bool
 227         True if the completion was successful, False otherwise
 228     """
 229     commandline = os.environ['COMMANDLINE']
 230     args = split_args(commandline)[1:]
 231     if args and not commandline.endswith(' '):
 232         incomplete = args[-1]
 233         args = args[:-1]
 234     else:
 235         incomplete = ''
 236 
 237     def escape(s):
 238         return s.replace('"', '""').replace("'", "''").replace('$', '\\$').replace('`', '\\`')
 239     res = []
 240     for item, help in get_choices(cli, prog_name, args, incomplete):
 241         if help:
 242             res.append(r'"%s"\:"%s"' % (escape(item), escape(help)))
 243         else:
 244             res.append('"%s"' % escape(item))
 245     if res:
 246         echo("_arguments '*: :((%s))'" % '\n'.join(res))
 247     else:
 248         echo("_files")
 249 
 250     return True

 253 def do_powershell_complete(cli, prog_name):
 254     """Do the powershell completion
 255 
 256     Parameters
 257     ----------
 258     cli : click.Command
 259         The main click Command of the program
 260     prog_name : str
 261         The program name on the command line
 262 
 263     Returns
 264     -------
 265     bool
 266         True if the completion was successful, False otherwise
 267     """
 268     commandline = os.environ['COMMANDLINE']
 269     args = split_args(commandline)[1:]
 270     quote = single_quote
 271     incomplete = ''
 272     if args and not commandline.endswith(' '):
 273         incomplete = args[-1]
 274         args = args[:-1]
 275         quote_pos = commandline.rfind(incomplete) - 1
 276         if quote_pos >= 0 and commandline[quote_pos] == '"':
 277             quote = double_quote
 278 
 279     for item, help in get_choices(cli, prog_name, args, incomplete):
 280         echo(quote(item))
 281 
 282     return True

 285 def get_code(shell=None, prog_name=None, env_name=None, extra_env=None):
 286     """Returns the completion code to be evaluated by the shell
 287 
 288     Parameters
 289     ----------
 290     shell : Shell
 291         The shell type (Default value = None)
 292     prog_name : str
 293         The program name on the command line (Default value = None)
 294     env_name : str
 295         The environment variable used to control the completion (Default value = None)
 296     extra_env : dict
 297         Some extra environment variables to be added to the generated code (Default value = None)
 298 
 299     Returns
 300     -------
 301     str
 302         The code to be evaluated by the shell
 303     """
 304     from jinja2 import Environment, FileSystemLoader
 305     if shell in [None, 'auto']:
 306         shell = get_auto_shell()
 307     if not isinstance(shell, Shell):
 308         shell = Shell[shell]
 309     prog_name = prog_name or click.get_current_context().find_root().info_name
 310     env_name = env_name or '_%s_COMPLETE' % prog_name.upper().replace('-', '_')
 311     extra_env = extra_env if extra_env else {}
 312     env = Environment(loader=FileSystemLoader(os.path.dirname(__file__)))
 313     template = env.get_template('%s.j2' % shell.name)
 314     return template.render(prog_name=prog_name, complete_var=env_name, extra_env=extra_env)

 317 def install(shell=None, prog_name=None, env_name=None, path=None, append=None, extra_env=None):
 318     """Install the completion
 319 
 320     Parameters
 321     ----------
 322     shell : Shell
 323         The shell type targeted. It will be guessed with get_auto_shell() if the value is None (Default value = None)
 324     prog_name : str
 325         The program name on the command line. It will be automatically computed if the value is None
 326         (Default value = None)
 327     env_name : str
 328         The environment variable name used to control the completion. It will be automatically computed if the value is
 329         None (Default value = None)
 330     path : str
 331         The installation path of the code to be evaluated by the shell. The standard installation path is used if the
 332         value is None (Default value = None)
 333     append : bool
 334         Whether to append the content to the file or to override it. The default behavior depends on the shell type
 335         (Default value = None)
 336     extra_env : dict
 337         A set of environment variables and their values to be added to the generated code (Default value = None)
 338     """
 339     prog_name = prog_name or click.get_current_context().find_root().info_name
 340     shell = shell or get_auto_shell()
 341     if append is None and path is not None:
 342         append = True
 343     if append is not None:
 344         mode = 'a' if append else 'w'
 345     else:
 346         mode = None
 347 
 348     if shell == 'fish':
 349         path = path or os.path.expanduser('~') + '/.config/fish/completions/%s.fish' % prog_name
 350         mode = mode or 'w'
 351     elif shell == 'bash':
 352         path = path or os.path.expanduser('~') + '/.bash_completion'
 353         mode = mode or 'a'
 354     elif shell == 'zsh':
 355         path = path or os.path.expanduser('~') + '/.zshrc'
 356         mode = mode or 'a'
 357     elif shell == 'powershell':
 358         subprocess.check_call(['powershell', 'Set-ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted -Scope CurrentUser'])
 359         path = path or subprocess.check_output(['powershell', '-NoProfile', 'echo $profile']).strip() if install else ''
 360         mode = mode or 'a'
 361     else:
 362         raise click.ClickException('%s is not supported.' % shell)
 363 
 364     if append is not None:
 365         mode = 'a' if append else 'w'
 366     else:
 367         mode = mode
 368     d = os.path.dirname(path)
 369     if not os.path.exists(d):
 370         os.makedirs(d)
 371     f = open(path, mode)
 372     f.write(get_code(shell, prog_name, env_name, extra_env))
 373     f.write("\n")
 374     f.close()
 375     return shell, path

 378 class Shell(Enum):
 379     bash = 'Bourne again shell'
 380     fish = 'Friendly interactive shell'
 381     zsh = 'Z shell'
 382     powershell = 'Windows PowerShell'
